/link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/adnAdbi.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Wnn05dW</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[reformedxile]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>In case you’re having a bad day</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Ly1gOV6</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/pVz1TfB.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Ly1gOV6</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[knightsLikeThisOnANightLikeThis]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Legendary performance</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/GNo0JeO</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/lKpHwxn.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/GNo0JeO</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sya5]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>The Honor Walk</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/K1uuzRc</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/PDv5Nzm.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Jarod Markus-Brooks. Born June 27th, 1998. Died February 11th, 2022. Aged 23 years.

February 14th 2022, 1am, John Muir Medical Center, Walnut Creek, California.

The photo attached is known as an "Honor Walk." It is often performed in hospitals when an organ donor, such as Jarod, offers his own body for the life of others. This was Jarod's Honor Walk, and is the last time I will ever see my son.

Although I think it was edited for time, these were the words I composed for the OR team to read aloud prior to their important task.

"For those of you in the OR right now: Like my son, you are all blessed. You are all beautiful. You are all essential. You have before you the body of my son. He was also blessed. He was also beautiful and to so many people, he was essential. I could say to you: 'The candle that burns twice as bright lasts half as long,' but Jarod was not one to appreciate cliches. Instead, I will say that his passion, his empathy and his fierce ability to love will live on far past his death through your hands.

When you are finished here, this important work, I would appreciate if you would do the following, in his honor: Please. Please call your children, your parents, your wife or your husband or your partner. Please tell them know how much you love them. How important they are to you. How you, above so many others, understand how fragile life is, but also how eternal love is. He would want this because he would often put others above himself. 

Embolden yourselves to live as Jarod did; unapologetically. While the Pandemic raged across the world, you were the sentinels, as Jarod, my son, my baby boy, was the sentinel and beacon of light to so many people in his life. This is our charge, our purpose and our meaning, right now. This moment. This unrecoverable speck of time. Because all moments are blessed. All moments are beautiful. All moments are essential.

And for Jarod, I want to say, my love for you is eternal. You are my son. I don’t know where you are headed but I do know that you will spread love, laughter, compassion, empathy and service to whoever you meet along the way.

For me, personally, I am gutted. I am wrecked. I am without comprehension. This is my son. My Light and my Life. I love him with every fiber of this mortal existence. I always knew that he was destined for great things. What I did not know is that great things meant sacrificing his life on this Earth. Go in peace, my son. Go with God. Go with the Eternal. Even though you are not with us physically, your Soul lives on. You are now set to do what you have always wanted to do: Help another. Bless you, my boy. 'You can finally rest.'"

So many people have reached out to me to show support. Many have asked if there is some gift they could give in Jarod's name. The most important gift I know he would want is what I've always said- take a moment to reach out to your loved ones, because time is far too short and far too fragile. If, however, you are interested in making a small donation in Jarod's name (Jarod Markus-Brooks):

For my healthcare friends, consider donating to Alameda Healthcare Foundation http://www.alamedahealthsystem.org/giving/ . AHS is where I found my purpose in healthcare and public service. They are the reason I do what I do.

If you are faith based, consider sending a small gift to the Pastor's Fund at Christ Episcopal Church in Alameda, CA https://christchurchalameda.org/ . Pastor Stephen McHale stood by me, my family and my son in his final moments.

To all my Aggies out there, consider the UC Davis Student Scholars Fund https://give.ucdavis.edu/UGSH/322613 . Jarod was passionate about UCD and was always, always willing to help other students.

It is fitting that Jarod gave gifts of life on February 14th, 2022. Not only is it Valentine's Day, but it also happens to be National Donor Day. Donating his organs on National Donor Day is definitely Jarod's style. If he was going to do something, he did it all the way. Although he may not be with us in life anymore, he definitely won life.

And remember, tell your loved ones you love them, every day. Forgive the small things. Work to heal the old wounds. Be compassionate. Be kind. Come from a place of love. Because, isn't that the greatest gift and the greatest way to honor those that went before us?</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/9pGqnaH.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Dog Tax: To all my imgurians- THANK YOU FOR YOUR COMPASSION, YOUR LOVE AND YOUR SUPPORT. It has not gone unnoticed. This is Maisie. She makes us smile in the darkest times. Please smile along with her.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/K1uuzRc</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[aceebrofb]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>bamboozled again</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/0UU1MqF</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/zdvTKq0.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/0UU1MqF</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[IlTerribile]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Olympic Curling or Superbowl? Hmm</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/qcMYlWZ</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/QWuPj3h.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Answer: Have maximum fun enjoying what you enjoy!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/qcMYlWZ</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[epicurusaquinas]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Yea why Charlie?</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/n1pdgen</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/JXIQYuB.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/oouRjdT.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/n1pdgen</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[GoodBadInternet]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Funny Random Meme an